abstract: Russian pranksters claim they called U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders pretending to be climate activist Greta Thunberg and offered Thunberg's support to his campaign.
snippet: Russian pranksters claim they called U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders pretending to be climate activist Greta Thunberg and offered Thunberg's support to his campaign.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russian pranksters claim they called U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Bernie Sanders pretending to be climate activist Greta Thunberg and offered Thunberg's support to his campaign.
headline_main: Bernie Sanders Pranked by Russians Posing as Greta Thunberg
headline_print_headline: Bernie Sanders Pranked by Russians Posing as Greta Thunberg

abstract: As the Democratic presidential race hurtles toward Nevada, candidates in the still-crowded field are jumping into their first test in a racially diverse state with solid union muscle and shaky plans for a presidential caucus.
snippet: As the Democratic presidential race hurtles toward Nevada, candidates in the still-crowded field are jumping into their first test in a racially diverse state with solid union muscle and shaky plans for a presidential caucus.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — As the Democratic presidential race hurtles toward Nevada, candidates in the still-crowded field are jumping into their first test in a racially diverse state with solid union muscle and shaky plans for a presidential caucus.
headline_main: Diversity Test: 2020 Democrats Seek Their Fortunes in Nevada
headline_print_headline: Diversity Test: 2020 Democrats Seek Their Fortunes in Nevada

abstract: A crucial question for the Vermont senator has always been whether he can expand his coalition. In a race this crowded, it’s unclear whether he even needs to do so.

abstract: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
snippet: A whipsaw week of charged decisions by the Justice Department, some favored by the president and others not, has bewildered much of Washington.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When President Trump learned that the Justice Department was dropping a case against a former F.B.I. official whom he considered one of his longtime enemies, his immediate response was anger. As he flipped on the television Friday and watched how the story was being covered, that anger only mounted.

abstract: Nevada is more diverse than Iowa and in many ways more reflective of the Democratic Party. And it has a different take on how caucuses should work.
snippet: Nevada is more diverse than Iowa and in many ways more reflective of the Democratic Party. And it has a different take on how caucuses should work.
lead_paragraph: After the chaos in Iowa, Nevada Democrats want to show the country what a caucus should look like.
